PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions About Our Ethereum Transaction Analysis App
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Our app analyzes new transactions on the Ethereum blockchain in real-time. It provides insights into transaction details, contract interactions, and on-chain activity.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: We connect directly to Ethereum nodes to stream incoming transactions. Advanced algorithms then parse and decode the transaction data to extract valuable information.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: What kind of analysis is provided?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: The app identifies token transfers, smart contract calls, internal transactions between contracts, and provides decoded input data. It also flags suspicious transactions based on heuristics.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: Yes, in addition to real-time monitoring, we also have a full archive of Ethereum transactions that can be queried and analyzed.
FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to common questions about our Ethereum transaction analysis app.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: Our app provides real-time analysis of new Ethereum transactions as they occur on the blockchain. It monitors the network, decodes transaction data, and provides insights into transaction types, token transfers, smart contract interactions, and more.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: We run Ethereum nodes that stream new block and transaction data. This data is then processed by our proprietary analytics engine that decodes transactions, maps addresses, and extracts relevant information to provide structured insights.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: What kind of insights can I get?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: You can view transaction hashes, sender/receiver addresses, ether value transfers, ERC20 token transfers, smart contract function calls, transaction status and more. Advanced filtering and search capabilities allow you to slice and dice the data.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Yes, our app stores all transaction data going back to the genesis block of Ethereum. You can query and analyze historical transactions in addition to new incoming transactions.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: Can I get notifications for certain transactions?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: Absolutely. You can set up customized alerts to be notified when specific addresses, contracts, or transaction types are involved in new transactions on the Ethereum network.
